-- Thailand’s Jaidee Wins Wales Open for First Golf Title in Europe
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-06-03T15:59:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/thailand-s-jaidee-wins-wales-open-for-first-golf-title-in-europe.html
Thailand ’s Thongchai Jaidee won an
event in Europe for a first time, finishing one shot clear at
golf’s Wales Open.  The 42-year-old finished on 6-under-par 278 after an 1-over
final round today at Celtic Manor, with Spain’s Gonzalo
Fernandez-Castano, South Africa’s Richard Sterne, Denmark’s
Thomas Bjoern and Joost Luiten of the Netherlands all on 5-
under.  Jaidee had four previous wins on the European Tour, but all
at events held in Asia. The most recent was at the Ballantine’s
Championship in  South Korea  in 2009.  Jaidee, who collects a check for 300,000 euros ($373,000),
had a double-bogey, three bogeys and four birdies today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  